    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mouth organs which have a rectangular body that terminates in a plastic mouthpiece. They are played via a keyboard corresponding to 12 notes, and usually have two or three octaves. There are various sizes, classed by range, including soprano, alto, tenor, and bass.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026541/Marcuse, Musical Instruments Dictionary (1975)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mondorgels met een rechthoekige romp die eindigt in een plastic mondstuk. Ze worden bespeeld als een blokfluit.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
